Publisher: Smithsonian Institution Press; Edition Not Stated edition (1995)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 0937311200
ISBN-13: 978-0937311202

The National Museum of American Art, dedicated to the art and artists who have contributed to our cultural heritage, provides insight into who we are as
a people. Originating in 1829 when the first objects were acquired for the future national collection, the extensive holdings now constitute an invaluable
record of our creativity, hopes, and concerns.
A measure of the size of the collections is the fact that this book can include only one percent of the museum's holdings.
